verbs.description: miseat (third-person singular simple present miseats, present participle miseating, simple past misate, past participle miseaten)

entries.meaning: (rare, intransitive) To eat badly or wrongly; to make poor dietary choices.
examples: […]  physicians, dieticians, teachers, and many others can assist you in the insight-gaining process, but you will be able to develop much of it yourself if you are willing to do so. Being aware of why you are miseating is a requirement in controlling this miseating.
